---------------------------------------------------------------------

How to use this demo.

Please read the uNabto SDK documentation for further details
about using the demo. http://nabto.com/documentation

Assuming you know the location of the AmelieSdk e.g. c:\AmelieSdk\v1.6.0.54 as of this writing.

1. Create a folder called Nabto in Projects\Amelie\COLApps\Apps
2. Copy the unabto folder to Projects\Amelie\COLApps\Apps\Nabto
3. goto unabto\demo\rtx4100\Build\RTX4100_WSAB or RTX4140_WSAB run ba.bat

---------------------------------------------------------------------

How to update the RTX41XX firmware:

Update module firmware:
1. Set SW3 to VIN
2. Run FwuRTX41xx_V0105_N0039.exe (or the newest version available)
3. Select COM4 (or first COM port installed)
4. Press down SW4 Boot while setting SW3 to USB

Update WiFi firmware (this should runs automatically):
1. Set SW3 to VIN then to USB (restart)
2. Setup "RTX EAI Port Server Configuration"
  - Set COM# to 4 (or first COM port installed)
  - Set Speed to 115200
  - See firmware update pdf for more details
3. Run FwuAR4100.exe (or the newest version available)

Update COLA application:
1. Run the COLA Controller Application
2 . Select Nabto.fwu
3. Click Update

